[38;5;141m> [0mNow address SEC-4 (ethical holdout guardrails) in The Honest Take section:[0m[0m
I'll modify the following file: [38;5;141mchapter07.10-optimal-intervention-timing-prediction.md[0m[38;5;244m (using tool: write)[0m
Purpose: Address SEC-4: add ethical holdout guardrails

[49m[38;5;9m- 607     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m The self-fulfilling prophecy problem is real and insidious. Your model gets better at identifying the right patients at the right time. You intervene. They don't have events. Your next training cycle sees "model flagged, no event" and learns to flag less aggressively. Over 2-3 retraining cycles, the model can degrade significantly. You need a holdout strategy (randomly withhold intervention for a small percentage of flagged patients) to maintain the training signal, and that raises ethical questions about withholding care from patients you believe are at risk.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The self-fulfilling prophecy problem is real and insidious. Your model gets better at identifying the right patients at the right time. You intervene. They don't have events. Your next training cycle sees "model flagged, no event" and learns to flag less aggressively. Over 2-3 retraining cycles, the model can degrade significantly. You need a holdout strategy (randomly withhold intervention for a small percentage of flagged patients) to maintain the training signal, and that raises ethical questions about withholding care from patients you believe are at risk.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few guardrails on holdout designs: they're only appropriate for low-intensity interventions (outreach calls, reminders) where standard of care is already met without the model. IRB review is required for any prospective holdout. Natural variation in care manager capacity creates quasi-experimental conditions without deliberate withholding, and that's often sufficient. Never withhold clinical interventions (medication changes, referrals) for model training purposes.
[0m[K
